comments.content: Well, it looks to me actually that the “GOOD SHOES” part is AutoScape, but i think the rest is different. The S and J look different on 2 occasions. hmm.

When I hear “DIN qualities” I usually look at [ITC Conduit](http://web.archive.org/web/20080423184637/http:/www.myfonts.com/fonts/itc/conduit/), but this time the G isn’t closed enough. Are you sure it isn’t DIN?

- Mike Yanega

Hmm, yeah, the thing is, it is more like DIN Engschrift, but not condensed.

I would just think its regular DIN, but the S isn’t correct. Unless they messed with only the S.
I’ve been trying some options but nothing so far.
